  "asset": null,
  "timeframe": null,
  "market_context": "Bearish market structure with prior bearish break of structure and supply zones. Price briefly rose above a supply zone, misleading novice traders into believing a reversal occurred.",
  "key_observation": "Price broke and closed above a supply zone not to reverse trend, but to mitigate upper supply and sweep liquidity—creating a false CHoCH that trapped longs.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified a bearish market structure with prior bearish BOS and associated supply zones.",
    "Step 2: Noted price moved up and broke/closed above the last supply zone, which novices misinterpreted as a valid CHoCH.",
    "Step 3: Clarified the upward move was not from an unmitigated demand zone but served to mitigate upper supply and act as inducement.",
    "Step 4: Explained that price used the supply zone as a breaker block to sweep liquidity (stop-losses of longs) before continuing downward."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "A valid CHoCH requires price to reverse from an unmitigated demand zone—not a supply zone used as inducement. False breakouts above supply often precede liquidity sweeps and trend continuation.",
